  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,86,"“You don’t have to run around chasing after [the hope that He will help you]; you don’t and you can’t manufacture it. Like so much in the realm of grace, you won’t acquire it by leaning on your own strength or on that of another person. There are no secret formulas or any magical mantras involved. …"
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,87,"“In fact, the part we play is important but actually very small; God has the larger portion of the task. Our part is to come unto Him in lowliness and simplicity, then we should worry not and fear not.”"
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,88,"Mosiah 5:13; see alsoJohn 17:3."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,89,"President Nelson has repeatedly called on us to “expand our circle of love to embrace the whole human family” (“Blessed Are the Peacemakers,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2002, 41). In May 2022 he told young adults that “labels can lead to judging and animosity. Anyabuseorprejudicetoward another because of nationality, race, sexual orientation, gender, educational degrees, culture, or other significant identifiers is offensive to our Maker” (“Choices for Eternity” [worldwide devotional for young adults, May 15, 2022], Gospel Library). And importantly, he said: “I grieve that our Black brothers and sisters the world over are enduring the pains of racism and prejudice. Today I call upon our members everywhere to lead out in abandoning attitudes and actions of prejudice. I plead with you to promote respect for all of God’s children” (“Let God Prevail,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2020, 94)."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,90,"“Prejudice is not consistent with the revealed word of God. Favor or disfavor with God depends on devotion to Him and His commandments, not on the color of a person’s skin or other attributes."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,91,"“… This includes prejudice based on race, ethnicity, nationality, tribe, gender, age, disability, socioeconomic status, religious belief or nonbelief, and sexual orientation” (General Handbook,38.6.14, Gospel Library)."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/13daines,Elder Robert M. Daines,92,"See1 Nephi 11:25."
