  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/27phillips,Elder Alan T. Phillips,64,"SeeMatthew 7:7–8;James 1:5."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/27phillips,Elder Alan T. Phillips,65,"“He [the Holy Ghost] is the Comforter (John 14:26). As the soothing voice of a loving parent can quiet a crying child, the whisperings of the Spirit can calm our fears, hush the nagging worries of our life, and comfort us when we grieve. The Holy Ghost can fill us ‘with hope and perfect love’ and ‘teach [us] the peaceable things of the kingdom’ (Moroni 8:26;Doctrine and Covenants 36:2)” (Topics and Questions, “Holy Ghost,” Gospel Library)."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/27phillips,Elder Alan T. Phillips,66,"“He [the Holy Ghost] ‘witnesses of the Father and the Son’ (2 Nephi 31:18). It is only through the power of the Holy Ghost that we can receive a sure testimony of God the Father and His Son, Jesus Christ."
  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/27phillips,Elder Alan T. Phillips,67,"“The Holy Ghost testifies of truth, and it is through His power that we ‘may know the truth of all things’ (Moroni 10:5)” (“The Holy Ghost Testifies of Truth,”Liahona, Mar. 2010, 14, 15)."
