  2023,"10",/general-conference/2023/10/28rasband,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,48,"The Osmond family was a popular American music group known for their pop songs. The group reached the height of fame in the mid-1970s, performing on television variety shows. Donny and Marie continued with television with stage careers, while the brothers performed for decades as country artists in Branson, Missouri."
